<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="497" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,989,1950]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1169,1194]" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Posterior prothoracic lobe of male with median and lateral portions separated by very slight incision, median portion with border straight (
<figureCitation box="[665,732,1205,1230]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); in female median and lateral portions not distinguishable and border of median portion slightly convex. Pterothorax with antehumeral pale stripe reaching about ¾ length of pterothorax (
<figureCitation box="[297,382,1277,1302]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1903,1926]" captionTargetBox="[195,1401,236,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1883]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Pterothorax in lateral view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (14); P. martinezi female, holotype (15); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype (16); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (17); P. pronoti female, holotype (18); P. quadratum male, holotype (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376930/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Venter pale with large black median stripe (
<figureCitation box="[904,990,1277,1302]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 24" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[280,1335,276,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 24. Venter in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (20); P. martinezi female, holotype (21); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype (22). P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (23); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376931/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Male Fw hyaline, without pale apical area, pseudostigma distinct. Hw hyaline, pseudostigma gray with seven cells (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1109,1313,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionTargetBox="[236,1360,265,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1940]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Wings in P. astictum male, Espírito Santo, Hw non saturated (25), saturated (26); female, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro, Hw non saturated (27) saturated (28)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376932/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
), becoming orange-yellow at high saturation (
<figureCitation box="[334,419,1349,1374]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionTargetBox="[236,1360,265,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1940]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Wings in P. astictum male, Espírito Santo, Hw non saturated (25), saturated (26); female, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro, Hw non saturated (27) saturated (28)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376932/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Border of Hw of male with elevation at level of pseudostigma. Female with white apical area reaching level of RP 
<quantity box="[436,478,1385,1410]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
both wings, with no distinct pseudostigma (
<figureCitation box="[975,1060,1385,1410]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionTargetBox="[236,1360,265,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1940]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Wings in P. astictum male, Espírito Santo, Hw non saturated (25), saturated (26); female, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro, Hw non saturated (27) saturated (28)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376932/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). At high saturation white area of Hw becomes light-blue with yellow venation, costal vein orange, and the pseudostigma becomes distinct with 11 cells (
<figureCitation box="[220,307,1457,1482]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionTargetBox="[236,1360,265,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1940]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Wings in P. astictum male, Espírito Santo, Hw non saturated (25), saturated (26); female, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro, Hw non saturated (27) saturated (28)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376932/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Anterior hamuli with ear-like basal plate, with posteromedial angle sclerotized. Distal portion of batilliform lamina curved ventrally with sclerotized apex. Posterior hamuli curved anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1261,1350,1493,1518]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 41" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[254,1339,240,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[165,1422,141,1955]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 41. Genitalia of second segment in P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro (37); P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (38); P. humaita sp. nov., holotype (39); P. minimum sp. nov., holotype (40); P. quadratum sp. nov., holotype (41)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376935/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
). Penis segment 
<quantity box="[251,293,1529,1554]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="4" pageNumber="497" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
ectal view (
<figureCitation box="[428,508,1529,1554]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 51" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[264,1319,197,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[204,1372,153,1898]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 51. Penis of P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro, in ectal (42) and lateral (43) views; P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in ectal (44) and lateral (45) views. P. humaita sp. nov. in ectal (46) and lateral (47) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in ectal (48) and lateral (49) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in ectal (50) and lateral views (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376936/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
) rectangular with no visible spines; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1085,1166,1529,1554]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 51" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[264,1319,197,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[204,1372,153,1898]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 51. Penis of P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro, in ectal (42) and lateral (43) views; P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in ectal (44) and lateral (45) views. P. humaita sp. nov. in ectal (46) and lateral (47) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in ectal (48) and lateral (49) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in ectal (50) and lateral views (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376936/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) with small median row of very short spines. Female cercus in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[752,837,1565,1590]" captionStart="FIGURES 52 – 53" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[315,1085,222,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[301,1286,135,1949]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 52 – 53. Female cercus in dorsal view: in P. astictum, Rio de Janeiro, Tinguá (52); P. martinezi, allotype (53)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376937/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) about as long as S10, parallel, conical, and pilose. Dorsoposterior portion of S10 V-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[653,745,1601,1626]" captionStart="FIGURES 52 – 53" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[315,1085,222,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[301,1286,135,1949]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 52 – 53. Female cercus in dorsal view: in P. astictum, Rio de Janeiro, Tinguá (52); P. martinezi, allotype (53)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376937/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor reaching about level of hind border of S10 posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[288,374,1637,1662]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 65" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[195,1367,190,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[180,1408,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 65. Abdomen S 8 – 10 in lateral view: in P. astictum, São Paulo, Jacareí (62). Ovipositor in lateral view: in P. astictum, Rio de Janeiro, Tinguá (63); P. martinezi, holotype (64); P. sp. (65)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376940/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Lateral valve with 9–10 minute, equal-sized teeth, except distal one larger (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1333,1637,1662]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 65" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[195,1367,190,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[180,1408,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 65. Abdomen S 8 – 10 in lateral view: in P. astictum, São Paulo, Jacareí (62). Ovipositor in lateral view: in P. astictum, Rio de Janeiro, Tinguá (63); P. martinezi, holotype (64); P. sp. (65)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376940/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="497">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Female similar to male, except for presence of pale apical area in Hw and for border with no elevation.
</paragraph>
